&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note for Welsh students, you must apply via Streamlining where all available jobs can be located’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a number of career opportunities for both newly qualified and experienced registrants who are passionate about delivering high quality, patient centered care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires motivation, enthusiasm, excellent communication skills and demonstration of evidence based clinical practice. The successful candidate should be motivated and enthusiastic about your own professional development and be open to undertaking further academic qualifications. They must be flexible, approachable, compassionate, motivated, hardworking and be able to manage their time effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liam Rowe - Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
